headline: Should ONEOK's (OKE) Strong Synergy Gains Offset Concerns Over a Moderated 2026 Outlook?
summary: ONEOK recently reported third-quarter results that exceeded expectations and announced achieving nearly US$500 million in acquisition synergies year-to-date, reflecting operational advances and growth in pipeline volumes and new project ramp-ups. An interesting insight is that these synergies and improved operational performance were delivered despite management moderating its 2026 outlook due to ongoing commodity price volatility.
